{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "nft-marketplace-api-v2",
    "name": "NFT Marketplace API v2",
    "description": "API endpoints for NFTCollection and NFTAuction smart contracts on Sepolia testnet.\n\nStart the server: `npm run api`\n\n⚠️ IMPORTANT: All write operations now require a `privateKey` in the request body instead of a `signer` role. Private keys are provided by the user via Postman, not from .env file.\n\nPrivate key format: Can be with or without 0x prefix (e.g. \"0xabc123...\" or \"abc123...\")",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "nftContractAddress",
      "value": "0x2e2c56f458fBdd3EB3099B1Ef1ec0B7bE832C7e7",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "auctionContractAddress",
      "value": "0xDF46504998e801A53Db5951B889734DEc5907a25",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "privateKey",
      "value": "your_private_key_here",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Your private key (with or without 0x prefix). Update this variable for each request or provide it directly in the body."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health Check",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": [""]
        },
        "description": "Returns API info, all available endpoints, contract addresses, and network information."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "NFTCollection",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Read",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Get Total Minted",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/total-minted",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "total-minted"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the total number of NFTs minted so far."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Collection Name",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/name",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "name"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the ERC721 collection name."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Collection Symbol",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/symbol",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "symbol"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the ERC721 collection symbol."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Creator of Token",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/creator/0",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "creator", "0"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the original minter (creator) of a token. Change the token ID in the URL."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Token URI",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/token-uri/0",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "token-uri", "0"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the metadata URI (IPFS link) for a token. Change the token ID in the URL."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Owner of Token",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/owner-of/0",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "owner-of", "0"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the current owner of a token. Change the token ID in the URL."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Balance of Address",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/balance-of/0x79E7165D44D2C1ff314F7D484d516656351605Df",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "balance-of", "0x79E7165D44D2C1ff314F7D484d516656351605Df"]
                },
                "description": "Returns how many NFTs an address owns. Replace the address in the URL."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Approved Address for Token",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/approved/0",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "approved", "0"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the address approved to transfer a specific token. Change the token ID in the URL."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Check Approval For All",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/is-approved-for-all/0x79E7165D44D2C1ff314F7D484d516656351605Df/{{auctionContractAddress}}",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "is-approved-for-all", "0x79E7165D44D2C1ff314F7D484d516656351605Df", "{{auctionContractAddress}}"]
                },
                "description": "Checks if an operator is approved to manage all NFTs of an owner. Replace owner and operator addresses in the URL."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Write",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Mint NFT",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"to\": \"0x79E7165D44D2C1ff314F7D484d516656351605Df\",\n  \"tokenURI\": \"ipfs://QmExample/metadata.json\",\n  \"privateKey\": \"{{privateKey}}\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/mint",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "mint"]
                },
                "description": "Mints a new NFT to the specified address.\n\nFields:\n- to: recipient address (can be your own address)\n- tokenURI: IPFS metadata URI\n- privateKey: your private key (with or without 0x prefix)\n\n⚠️ Anyone can mint - no restrictions."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Approve Token",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"to\": \"{{auctionContractAddress}}\",\n  \"tokenId\": 0,\n  \"privateKey\": \"{{privateKey}}\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/approve",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "approve"]
                },
                "description": "Approves an address (e.g. the Auction contract) to transfer a specific token.\n\nFields:\n- to: address to approve (usually auction or marketplace contract)\n- tokenId: token ID to approve\n- privateKey: must be the token owner's private key"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Set Approval For All",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"operator\": \"{{auctionContractAddress}}\",\n  \"approved\": true,\n  \"privateKey\": \"{{privateKey}}\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/set-approval-for-all",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "set-approval-for-all"]
                },
                "description": "Grants or revokes an operator permission to manage ALL of your tokens.\n\nFields:\n- operator: address to grant/revoke (e.g. auction contract)\n- approved: true to grant, false to revoke\n- privateKey: token owner's private key"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Transfer NFT",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"from\": \"0x79E7165D44D2C1ff314F7D484d516656351605Df\",\n  \"to\": \"0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000001\",\n  \"tokenId\": 0,\n  \"privateKey\": \"{{privateKey}}\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/nft/transfer",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "nft", "transfer"]
                },
                "description": "Transfers an NFT between addresses.\n\nFields:\n- from: current owner address\n- to: recipient address\n- tokenId: token to transfer\n- privateKey: must be owner's or approved address's private key"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "NFTAuction",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Read",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Get Total Auctions",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/total-auctions",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "total-auctions"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the total number of auctions ever created."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Platform Fee",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/platform-fee",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "platform-fee"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the current platform fee percentage (e.g. 250 = 2.5%)."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Active Auctions",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/active",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "active"]
                },
                "description": "Returns all currently active (not expired, not finalized) auctions."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Auctions By Seller",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/by-seller/0x79E7165D44D2C1ff314F7D484d516656351605Df",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "by-seller", "0x79E7165D44D2C1ff314F7D484d516656351605Df"]
                },
                "description": "Returns all auctions created by a specific seller. Replace the address in the URL."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Auctions Won By Address",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/won-by/0x7628fa6C917E9da45a4948410cB54869190248Fb",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "won-by", "0x7628fa6C917E9da45a4948410cB54869190248Fb"]
                },
                "description": "Returns all auctions won by a specific address. Replace the address in the URL."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Pending Returns",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/pending-returns/0x7628fa6C917E9da45a4948410cB54869190248Fb",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "pending-returns", "0x7628fa6C917E9da45a4948410cB54869190248Fb"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the amount of ETH pending to be withdrawn by an address (from outbid refunds). Replace the address in the URL."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Contract Balance",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/contract-balance",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "contract-balance"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the native ETH balance of the NFTAuction contract. Use this before and after actions (bids/finalize) to see balance changes."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Auction By ID",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/0",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "0"]
                },
                "description": "Returns full details of a specific auction. Change the auction ID in the URL."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get Auction Bidders",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/0/bidders",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "0", "bidders"]
                },
                "description": "Returns the list of all bidder addresses for an auction. Change the auction ID in the URL."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Write",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Create Auction",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"nftContract\": \"{{nftContractAddress}}\",\n  \"tokenId\": 0,\n  \"minPrice\": \"0.001\",\n  \"duration\": 300,\n  \"privateKey\": \"{{privateKey}}\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/create",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "create"]
                },
                "description": "Creates a new auction for an NFT. The signer must own the token and have approved the auction contract.\n\n⚠️ No listing fee required - creating an auction is free!\n\nFields:\n- nftContract: NFTCollection contract address\n- tokenId: token to auction\n- minPrice: minimum bid in ETH (e.g. \"0.001\")\n- duration: auction duration in seconds (e.g. 300 = 5 minutes)\n- privateKey: token owner's private key"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Place Bid",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"auctionId\": 0,\n  \"bidAmount\": \"0.002\",\n  \"privateKey\": \"{{privateKey}}\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/bid",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "bid"]
                },
                "description": "Places a bid on an active auction. Bid must be >= minPrice and > current highest bid.\n\nFields:\n- auctionId: ID of the auction\n- bidAmount: bid amount in ETH (e.g. \"0.002\")\n- privateKey: bidder's private key (anyone can bid)"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Finalize Auction",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"auctionId\": 0,\n  \"privateKey\": \"{{privateKey}}\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/finalize",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "finalize"]
                },
                "description": "Finalizes an expired auction. On-chain logic handles:\n- Winner selection (highest bidder)\n- NFT transfer to winner\n- Seller receives winning bid minus 2.5% platform fee\n- Platform fee sent to contract owner\n- All outbid bidders automatically refunded\n\nIf no bids exist, NFT is returned to seller.\n\nFields:\n- auctionId: ID of the auction to finalize\n- privateKey: anyone can call this after expiry (typically seller)"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Relist NFT From Previous Auction (Winner Only, Optional)",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"previousAuctionId\": 0,\n  \"minPrice\": \"0.0015\",\n  \"duration\": 300,\n  \"privateKey\": \"{{privateKey}}\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/relist-from-auction",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "relist-from-auction"]
                },
                "description": "Optional convenience endpoint: lets the *winner* of a previous auction start a new auction for the **same NFT**.\n\nRequirements:\n- The previous auction must be finalized with a winner (highestBidder != 0).\n- The caller's private key must belong to the previous auction winner.\n\nWhat this endpoint does automatically:\n1. Verifies you are the winner of the previous auction.\n2. Checks if the NFTAuction contract is approved for this specific token.\n3. If not approved, automatically submits an `approve()` transaction for the token (returns hash immediately, no waiting).\n4. Immediately submits a `createAuction()` transaction for the same NFT.\n5. Returns both transaction hashes instantly (fast response ~2-3 seconds).\n\n⚠️ Important: If approval was needed, the `auctionTransactionHash` may revert if the approval transaction hasn't confirmed yet. In that case, wait for the approval to confirm, then retry this endpoint (it will skip approval if already approved).\n\nFields:\n- previousAuctionId: ID of the auction that was won.\n- minPrice: new minimum bid in ETH for the re-auction (e.g. \"0.0015\").\n- duration: new auction duration in seconds.\n- privateKey: private key of the previous winner (current NFT owner)."
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Set Platform Fee (Owner Only)",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Content-Type",
                    "value": "application/json"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"newFeePercentage\": 250,\n  \"privateKey\": \"{{privateKey}}\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auction/set-platform-fee",
                  "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
                  "path": ["api", "auction", "set-platform-fee"]
                },
                "description": "Updates the platform fee percentage. Only the contract owner can call this.\n\n250 = 2.5%, 500 = 5%, max 1000 = 10%\n\nFields:\n- newFeePercentage: new fee (e.g. 250 for 2.5%)\n- privateKey: contract owner's private key"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
